steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"ebil5","text":"We test doubling dilutions of each extract fraction in duplicate with a maximum concentration of  . Each round of screening also requires a control plate containing the solvent the extract was dissolved in (e.g. DMSO), an antibiotic (to be used as a positive control, e.g. erythromycin), and broth (negative control to test the growth of the testing organism). Using the plate layout described in Figure 1, each plate can contain either one complete set of a crude extract and five fractions of decreasing polarity, or the appropriate controls for the testing round. {"blocks":[{"key":"5gk9i","text":"Plate three technical replicates of each dilution onto a MHA plate. Incubate agar plates upside down at 37 °C overnight. Count the colonies the following day.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"988os","text":"We use a Perkin Elmer Victor X plate luminometer set to read 96 well plates with an integration time of 1 second per well. If we haven’t filled the entire plate, we change the settings so that the machine doesn’t measure the empty wells.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"87djr","text":"We take measurements immediately after setting up the plate (t=0) and then at 2, 4, 6, and 24 hours. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ahb55","text":"After the final timepoint, if the light has reduced to background levels in any of the wells (for our machine this is \u003c 10 relative light units [RLU])  plate 3 x 10 µL aliquots from each \"dark\" well onto fresh MHA to check for bacterial viability. We define the minimum bactericidal concentration (MBC) as the lowest concentration at which no colonies appear after overnight incubation at 37 °C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aald6","text":"Between measurements, place lids on the plates, put them in a plastic box lined with damp paper towels, and incubate at 37 °C with shaking at 100 RPM.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7fhi7","text":"Measure the optical density of the overnight culture of E. coli at 600nm (OD600).
